Test SVG output after applying JavaScript? Is there some way we can
apply the JavaScript non-interactively and then check the results?
http://phantomjs.org/

customizable alpha/color/size/etc for mouseovered/selected geoms. One
way to do this is by defining new *.hover aesthetics,
e.g. https://github.com/rstudio/ggvis/blob/master/demo/hover.r Another
way to do something similar is to just use
e.g. geom_point(aes(clickSelects=var))+
geom_point(aes(showSelected=var), colour="red", size=5)
Could we create a make_selecter() shortcut that does this?

